    public class TestBigdataNativeServiceEvaluation
extends AbstractDataDrivenSPARQLTestCase
    Data driven test suite for SPARQL 1.1 Federated Query against an internal, bigdata "aware" service (similar to our integrated full text search facility).
    Version:
    $Id: TestServiceInternal.java 6053 2012-02-29 18:47:54Z thompsonbry $ TODO Write test which uses a variable for the service reference, but where the service always resolves to a known service.         A simple SERVICE query against an INTERNAL service. The service adds in a single solution which restricts the set of solutions for the overall query. 
         PREFIX dc:    
 PREFIX :      
 PREFIX ns:    
 
 SELECT ?book ?title ?price
 {
    SERVICE  {
        ?book :foo :bar
    }.
    ?book dc:title ?title ;
          ns:price ?price .
 }

      • test_service_002

        public void test_service_002()
                      throws Exception
        A simple SERVICE query against an INTERNAL service. The service provides three solutions, two of which join with the remainder of the query.

        Note: Since the SERVICE is not actually doing joins, we wind up with duplicate solutions. 

         PREFIX dc:    
 PREFIX :      
 PREFIX ns:    
 
 SELECT ?book ?title ?price
 {
    SERVICE  {
        ?book :foo :bar
    }.
    hint:Prior hint:runFirst true .
    ?book dc:title ?title ;
          ns:price ?price .
 }
        Throws:
        Exception
